Sub-Sahara Africa Stocks: Diamond Bank of Nigeria, Fidelity Bank

-- B y   C h r i s   K a y
-- 
2011-06-01T16:17:37Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-01/sub-sahara-africa-stocks-diamond-bank-of-nigeria-fidelity-bank.html
The Ghana Stock Exchange Composite
Index snapped two days of gains, slipping less than 0.1 percent
to 1,161.93 by the 3 p.m. close in Accra.  Namibia ’s FTSE/ Namibia Overall Index (FTN098)  dropped 1.4 percent to
856.40 by the 4 p.m. end of trading in Windhoek. The Nigerian
Stock Exchange All-Share Index advanced for the fourth day,
gaining less than 0.1 percent to 25,875.31 by the 2:30 p.m.
close in Lagos, according to an e-mail from the bourse.
Mauritius’s SEMDEX Index advanced for the second day, climbing
0.1 percent to 2,081.04 by the 1:30 p.m. close in  Port Louis .
Kenya’s All-Share Index was closed for holiday.  The following shares rose or fell in sub-Saharan  Africa ,
excluding  South Africa . Stock symbols are in parentheses.  Diamond Bank Plc (DIAMONDB)  , a Nigerian lender, rallied
12 kobo, or 2 percent, to 6 naira, the biggest gain since May
26, after the central bank approved in principle its application
for an international license.  Fidelity Bank Plc (FIDELITY)  ,
jumped 9 kobo, or 3.5 percent, to 2.69 naira, the biggest
increase since May 20.  To contact the reporter on this story:
